<FeaturePage
  title="Job Scheduler"
  description="A durable, local-first job scheduler built into the engine. Retries, queues, and cross-session tasks — no extra infrastructure."
  badge="Core · Library"
  activePath="/features"
>
  <p>
    Most apps need background work: retries for failed requests, deferred uploads, scheduled
    reminders, webhooks. sp00ky ships with a built-in scheduler so you don’t have to bolt on a
    queue service.
  </p>
  <p>
    Jobs are persisted on-device, survive reloads, and replay across sessions. Define them
    declaratively, hand them to sp00ky, and let the scheduler worry about retries and backoff.
  </p>
  <h2>What you get</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Durable queues that survive reloads and crashes.</li>
    <li>Exponential backoff, configurable retry policies.</li>
    <li>Cross-tab coordination so jobs run exactly once.</li>
    <li>First-class hooks for progress, cancellation, and completion.</li>
  </ul>
</FeaturePage>
